      "content": "The following is an extract of the proposal posted on the [Idle governance forum](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdc-by-wincent/1188).\n\n### Summary\nA proposal to add the Wincent Clearpool USDC Yield Tranche as a new yield source for the USDC Best Yield vaults.\n\n### References\n* [Clearpool YTs as a new yield source for USDT BY - Fasanara](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdt-by-fasanara/1153) post\n* [Clearpool YTs as a new yield source for USDC BY - Portofino](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdc-by-portofino/1151) post\n* [Clearpool YTs as a new yield source for USDC BY - Fasanara](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdc-by-fasanara/1166) post\n* [Wincent](https://www.wincent.co/) website\n\n## Proposal\n\nAfter the successful integration of multiple Clearpool YTs in the [USDC](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdc-by-fasanara/1166) and [USDT](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdt-by-fasanara/1153) markets, this new proposal aims to add the latest Clearpool Yield Tranche to the Best Yield USDC vaults:\n\n* Clearpool USDC (Wincent) YTs, with specs available on GitHub [here](https://github.com/Idle-Finance/best-yield-PYT-strategy/blob/master/src/Contract.sol)\n\nSimilar to previous Clearpool's integration, Wincent's one would benefit doubly the Idle users\n\n> By integrating Clearpool USDC (Senior) tranches as a new yield source for the USDC BY strategy, we can create a two-side benefit for the Idle protocol:\n> \n> 1. The USDC BY strategy can add a new yield source, besides the usual Aave and Compound, able to offer an average APY in the 5% to 10% range. Currently, [Aave](https://app.aave.com/reserve-overview/?underlyingAsset=0xa0b86991c6218b36c1d19d4a2e9eb0ce3606eb48&marketName=proto_mainnet) and [Compound](https://compound.finance/markets/USDC) offer APYs lower than 1%. This significant increase in yield can benefit current BY LPs and attract new users to the protocol.\n> 2. The USDC BY funds flowing to the Senior side of Clearpool PYTs can create a stable source of funding for the Senior tranches and consequently incentive new Junior liquidity deployments thanks to the boosted APYs available (with an expected average APY in the range of 10% to 20%).\n\n[Yield Tranches](https://docs.idle.finance/products/perpetual-yield-tranches) are live since [December 2021](https://medium.com/idle-finance/make-yield-your-own-perpetual-yield-tranches-are-live-2aef53c153d6) holding a cumulative TVL of up to $50m.\n\n### Wincent details\n\n> Wincent is a leading crypto market maker with $3B+ daily volume and 300K+ daily transactions.\n>\n> Since 2018, Wincent develops software for algorithmic trading and market analysis.\n> Our true edge lies in our talented team with experience from Google, Facebook, academia, data science, competitive programming, math and physics competitions (IOI, IMO, IPhO, ACM ICPC), sports betting and poker.\n> Our algorithms trade $300 million – $3.5 billion daily on the top cryptocurrency exchanges worldwide 24/7/365.\n\n[Clearpool (Wincent) pool](https://clearpool.finance/permissionless/pools/0xa0749f550a336b031f63bd095062204e1a56055b?market=ethereum) is live since the beginning of September. The Wincent pool has a maximum borrowing capacity of up to $27m. [Credora](https://credora.io/) rates the borrower with a BB.\n\n| Protocol | Borrower | Capacity | Pool size | Credora's rating |\n| --- | --- | ---: | ---: | :---: |\n| Clearpool | Wincent | $27,000,000 | $ - | BB |\n\nAt the time of writing, the Wincent pool has been deployed and will soon start the borrowing activities.\n\n### Risk rating\n\nThe borrower has been already analysed internally following the [risk rating framework](https://gov.idle.finance/t/risk-framework-version-1/1143/3). The Clearpool (Wincent) Yield Tranches can be considered as a valid market to become a new yield source of the Best Yield vaults. \n\nIn order to trigger any BY deployment, the Yield Tranches will need to have at least a 30% coverage on Senior funds coming from the Junior counterparty.\n\n![image](ipfs://bafkreifilghj6oxj73dxytsyiw2dznfho5gmh6uuqep7mlkpfuwtmjpsqe)",
