      "content": "The following is an extract of the proposals posted on the Idle governance forum.\n\n* [Clearpool YTs as a new yield source for USDC BY - Portofino](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdc-by-portofino/1151) post\n* [Clearpool YTs as a new yield source for USDT BY - Fasanara](https://gov.idle.finance/t/clearpool-yts-as-a-new-yield-source-for-usdt-by-fasanara/1153) post\n\n### Author\nTreasury League\n\n### Summary\nA proposal to add the Portofino Clearpool USDC Yield Tranches and the Fasanara Clearpool USDT Yield Tranches as new yield sources for the USDC and the USDT Best Yield strategies.\n\n## Background\n\nAfter the recent exploit on Euler, Leagues have suggested to remove the Euler Yield Tranches from the basket of yield source of Best Yield strategies as a precautionary measure before a new audit is completed.\n\nThe current yield source of the Best Yield strategies would then be: \n\n| Strategy | Token | Underlying markets | \n| --- | --- | --- | \n| Senior BY | DAI | Aave, Compound, ~~Euler~~ | \n| Junior BY | DAI | ~~Euler~~, Morpho | \n\n## Proposal\n\nThese proposals aim to add new Clearpool Yield Tranches to the Best Yield strategies based on USDC and USDT:\n\n1.  [Clearpool USDC (Portofino) YTs](https://app.idle.finance/#/earn/protected-yield/0x9cacd44cfdf22731bc99facf3531c809d56bd4a2), with specs available on GitHub [here](https://github.com/Idle-Finance/best-yield-PYT-strategy/blob/master/src/Contract.sol)\n2. [Clearpool USDT (Fasanara) YTs](https://app.idle.finance/#/earn/protected-yield/0x0a6f2449c09769950cfb76f905ad11c341541f70), with specs available on GitHub [here](https://github.com/Idle-Finance/best-yield-PYT-strategy/blob/master/src/Contract.sol)\n\n## 1. Portofino details\n\n> Portofino technologies is a high-frequency trading market maker that uses borrowed funds as trading capital, providing superior returns thanks to its advanced machine learning & stochastic control techniques.\n\n[Clearpool (Portofino) pool](https://clearpool.finance/permissionless/pools/0x4a90c14335e81829d7cb0002605f555b8a784106?market=ethereum) is live since early March. The Portofino pool has a size of ~$4.7m and a maximum borrowing capacity of up to $28m. [Credora](https://credora.io/) rates the borrower with an A.\n\n| Protocol | Borrower | Capacity | Pool size | Credora's rating |\n| --- | --- | ---: | ---: | :---: | \n| Clearpool | Portofino | $28,624,138 | 4,754,744 | A |\n\nAt the time of writing, the Portofino pool provides 10.99% APR with a 64% utilization rate ([source](https://clearpool.finance/permissionless/pools/0x4a90c14335e81829d7cb0002605f555b8a784106?market=ethereum)).\n\n### Risk rating\n\nFollowing the new version of the [risk rating framework](https://gov.idle.finance/t/risk-framework-version-1/1143/3), the Clearpool (Portofino) Yield Tranches can be considered as a valid market to become a new yield source of the Best Yield strategies. \n\nIn order to trigger any BY deployment, the Yield Tranches will need to have at least a **30% coverage** on Senior funds coming from the Junior counterparty. \n\n## 2. Fasanara details\n\n> Fasanara Digital is a quantitative investment fund applying a scientific approach to investing in cryptoassets with the aim to achieve exceptional risk-adjusted returns for its investors.\n>\n> Fasanara Digital was started in 2019 as part of [Fasanara Capital](https://www.fasanara.com/), a 200 people London-based hedge fund founded in 2011 that specializes in alternative credit and fintech strategies. Overall, Fasanara Capital manages more than $4 billion across different funds.\n>\n> With a team of 15 people fully dedicated to investments and development in digital assets, Fasanara Digital manages a delta-neutral high turnover fund specialized in market-making and arbitrage strategies. The fund trades approximately $10 billion per month in volume on both spot and derivatives on all major trading venues and has approximately $75 million in equity.\n\n[Clearpool (Fasanara) pool](https://clearpool.finance/permissionless/pools/0x1a1d778776542c2efed161ba1fbcfe6e09ba99fb?market=ethereum) is live since the end of March. The Fasanara pool has a size of ~$1m and a maximum borrowing capacity of up to $40m. [Credora](https://credora.io/) rates the borrower with an AA.\n\n| Protocol | Borrower | Capacity | Pool size | Credora's rating |\n| --- | --- | ---: | ---: | :---: |\n| Clearpool | Portofino | $40,390,683 | 1,152,804 | AA |\n\nAt the time of writing, the Fasanara pool provides 14.25% APR with a 76% utilization rate ([source](https://clearpool.finance/permissionless/pools/0x1a1d778776542c2efed161ba1fbcfe6e09ba99fb?market=ethereum)).\n\n### Risk rating\n\nFollowing the new version of the [risk rating framework](https://gov.idle.finance/t/risk-framework-version-1/1143/3), the Clearpool (Fasanara) Yield Tranches can be considered as a valid market to become a new yield source of the Best Yield strategies. \n\nIn order to trigger any BY deployment, the Yield Tranches will need to have at least a **24% coverage** on Senior funds coming from the Junior counterparty. ",
