      "content": "### Summary\n\nThis proposal focus on one key initiative:\n\n* Remove part of the listed tokens from Idle Best Yield: RAI, SUSD, TUSD.\n\n## Rationale\n\nFollowing the recent decision of the Aave's community (see [Aave’s AIP-121](https://app.aave.com/governance/proposal/?proposalId=121))\n\n> A proposal to make parameter changes on Aave V2 ETH. Given that the market situation of these assets is currently volatile, out of an abundance of caution, we recommend temporarily freezing the following markets:\n>  […]\n> * sUSD\n> * RAI \n\nWe plan to update accordingly the assets listed in the Idle Best Yield, i.e. remove sUSD and RAI. \n\nIn addition, we plan to delist TUSD token. These three assets have never reached a sufficient level of traction to justify the rebalance costs incurred by Idle DAO’s smart contracts. \n\nThis initiative aligns with the previous proposal to delist FEI and other PYTs tokens. \n\n> Both BY and PYTs strategies require a good deal of ongoing bandwidth to ensure users have a quality experience. Idle Leagues have been monitoring the performances of the strategies (as reported in the [M2-2022 performance report](https://2235025969-files.gitbook.io/~/files/v0/b/gitbook-x-prod.appspot.com/o/spaces%2F-Lw-v0NTae0RVW1spR9R%2Fuploads%2F2ATYYtmXa6X6sRUxMkqG%2FM2-2022%20Performance%20Report.pdf?alt=media&token=bb721bc4-d4ff-44bb-990c-f1a80510225c)), and due to low-profit margins or other externalities (e.g. [FEI dissolution](https://tribe.fei.money/t/tip-121-proposal-for-the-future-of-the-tribe-dao/4475)) we decided to keep in the main dashboard only the strategies with the most traction and efficiency.\n\nThese four tokens won’t be anymore listed in the main UI under Best Yield, and deposits will no longer be available. Users will still be able to redeem their funds from either the [beta version of our dashboard](https://beta.idle.finance/) or by interacting with the contracts on [Etherscan](https://docs.idle.finance/developers/networks-and-codebase/ethereum-mainnet).",
