      "title": "[Temperature check] - Single Idle staking ",
      "content": "### Summary\nIn order to guarantee sustainable staking rewards, the Idle Leagues simulated different staking model scenarios and FeeCollector distribution weights. \n\nWith the help of the [$IDLE Staking Calculator](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/12JBKXGaicbOm45ttneUyyXtStMxzIYATvpvMjOHXABI/edit?usp=sharing) and also analysing the [Rebalancer Cost Outlook](https://duneanalytics.com/idle.finance/Rebalancer-Cost-Outlook) in order to come up with an optimal allocation, the Treasury League suggest the following weights: **50% staking rewards + 30% rebalancer + 10% fee treasury + 10% smart treasury**\nForum [Discussion link](https://gov.idle.finance/t/single-idle-staking/503)\n### Details\nThe current FeeCollector weights are currently: 80% Smart Treasury, 15% Fee Treasury, 5% Rebalancer. \nTo give token holders the opportunity to get maximum rewards out of all the options evaluated while allowing the protocol to pursue its sustainability, the Treasury League suggests changing the split of the FeeCollector weight to: **50% staking rewards + 30% rebalancer + 10% fee treasury + 10% smart treasury.**\nIt’s the Treasury League opinion that this is a balanced redistribution. Suggested weights would still cover the rebalance expenses, the flow to the fee treasury would still be sustainable and fees would still flow to the smart treasury.\n \n### Voting Options\nPlease cast your vote on one of the following options to decide if you are for or against the changes of the proposed weights for the FeeCollector:\n1.       FOR\n2.      AGAINST",
