      "title": "[Temperature Check] -- B2B Affiliate Program Kickoff",
      "content": "### Summary\n\nTo foster Idle protocol’s growth, and reduce the initial onboarding barriers for integrators and partners, we would like to propose a referral program for B2B partners.\n\nDespite the fact there are some direct (attractive yields/rewards) and indirect (fewer maintenance costs and increased capital resiliency) benefits in integrating Idle protocol into third-party services, we observed that adding an affiliate program would enhance new integrations.\n\nThe goal of this proposal is to set up an initial off-chain mechanism powered by the Pilot League.\n\n### Details\n\nDuring phase 1, the Pilot League committee would collect a list of integration partners and track the Partner Deposited Assets (PDA) along the time.\n\nProfit-sharing is triggered when a withdrawal event happens on partner funds, allowing the protocol to claim the accrued fees.\nThe Pilot League shares the profits in $IDLE tokens, at the conversion rate available on the market.\n\nProgram Parameters:\n* Program Budget: 50,000 $IDLE\n* Program Manager: Pilot League committee\n* Minimum threshold to execute the fee sharing: 500 $IDLE\n* Vesting period: linear unlock in 3 months\n\nMore details on referral levels and operations here: [B2B Affiliate Program Kickoff](https://gov.idle.finance/t/b2b-affiliate-program-kickoff/312)\nThe program will run for 3 months to test the parameters and collect feedback, and will then be officialized into an automated on-chain program.\n\n### Voting Options\n\nVote “**In favor**”, if you agree to kick off this Affiliate Program.\n\nVote “**Against**”, if you don't agree to kick off this Affiliate Program.\n\nVote “**Discuss more**”, if you have concerns about the implementation approach.\n\nSnapshot is an off-chain solution to cast a vote by signature, no gas spent.\n\n",
